OL,6,FOn Thursday 13 February 2025, Knox was
OL,7,Fsentenced at Canterbury Crown Court to
OL,8,Ftwo years and one month in prison.
OL,10,FSmith had breached a previous
OL,11,Fsuspended sentence and was jailed for
OL,12,Ftwo years and ten months.
OL,14,FChief Inspector Mark Stubberfield
OL,15,Fsaid: "Knox was determined to escape
OL,16,Fby any means but was tackled to the
OL,17,Fground by our responding officers,
OL,18,Fwhose tenacious bravery and
OL,19,Fprofessionalism ensured he was
OL,20,Fdisarmed and that both men have
OL,21,Fultimately now been brought to justice.
